## What This Project Is

This project is an **Obsidian plugin** (“Project Browser”) designed to help people navigate vault files and folders using a **non-technical, low-effort browsing interface** (ideal when you’re busy or don’t want to think in paths/structure). It replaces the new tab view with a browsable, searchable file/folder layout (see `manifest.json` for the concise plugin description).

## Folder Structure

```
src/              — Plugin source (Obsidian entrypoint, React UI, logic, styles, assets)
tests/            — Unit/component test scaffolding and E2E specs/helpers
docs/             — Project documentation (features, settings, testing, known issues)
scripts/          — Release, QA, and test automation scripts
qa-test-vault/    — Generated vault used for E2E/manual QA (created/filled by scripts)
dist/             — Build output (generated; used by Obsidian + E2E runner)
```

## Architecture Notes

The plugin bundles to `dist/` via esbuild and is loaded by Obsidian. The entrypoint (`src/main.ts`) registers the plugin behaviour/UI, including the “new tab replacement” browsing experience. UI is primarily React-based, with state handled via Jotai (UI state) and Redux Toolkit (structured workflow/app state where useful). Styles are built from CSS/SCSS and emitted alongside the plugin bundle.

## Key Constraints

- The plugin must remain compatible with Obsidian’s plugin API and packaging expectations (e.g. built assets in `dist/`, manifest copied into `dist/`).
- Don’t assume a backend/server exists — this is a local Obsidian plugin.
- E2E tests run Obsidian via WebdriverIO; do not start background services as part of automation tasks in this repo.
